- Fixed allocations are wasteful; use flexible arrays/containers.
- Recursion for DP is slow; prefer bottom-up/iterative DP.
- Full memset is costly if 'n' is small; only initialize needed elements.
- Using cin/cout is slower than scanf/printf.
